# TanStack Start (Cloudflare Workers)

`apps/web` is the only web deployable, hosted on Cloudflare Workers via `@cloudflare/vite-plugin` and Wrangler.

## Routes and data

- Route files coordinate URL parsing, loaders, pending/error states, metadata, and feature composition. They do not contain competitive rules or persistence queries.
- Prefer SSR loaders and server functions for initial authorized data.
- Validate all route params, search params, form data, and HTTP bodies at the inbound boundary.
- Keep filters, selected encounter, tab, and shareable view state in typed URLs when users expect deep links.
- Permission-specific data is selected on the server. Hiding controls is presentation only.
- Freshness aids trigger an authorized refetch; never merge untrusted broadcasts into canonical state.

## Server entrypoints

- Server functions, `/api/v1/*`, queue consumers, and cron handlers call shared application use cases.
- Auth routes delegate to the Better Auth adapter.
- Server-only modules, secrets, D1/R2 clients, and provider SDKs must not enter client bundles.
- Read Worker bindings from `env` / composition — do not assume Node `process.env` at module scope on Workers.
- Durable EA sync work is persisted and queued before the request returns.
- Map expected failures to typed safe responses with `code`, `messageKey`, and `requestId`.

## Rendering and UX

- Preserve loading, empty, stale, permission, and recoverable-error states across SSR and hydration.
- Avoid client-only rendering for public landing/portal content that benefits from SEO.
- Encounter detail uses deep links appropriate to desktop/mobile patterns adopted in the scaffold.

Build, preview, and deploy through Wrangler-compatible root scripts once scaffolded.
